🚀 Odoo 19 Enterprise Deployment Guide (2026 Edition)

This guide provides a professional, production-ready setup for Odoo 19
Enterprise using Docker, PostgreSQL 16, and Caddy for automatic SSL (HTTPS).

📋 Prerequisites

  - VPS: Ubuntu 24.04 LTS or higher.
  - Hardware: Minimum 2 vCPU / 4GB RAM.
  - Domain: A domain name (e.g., odoo.example.com) with an A Record pointing to
    your VPS IP.

🛠️ 1. Environment Setup

Run these commands on your clean VPS:

# Update system
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

# Install Docker
curl -fsSL https://get.docker.com -o get-docker.sh && sudo sh get-docker.sh

# Install Git
sudo apt install -y git

📂 2. Project Structure

Create the project folder and merge the Odoo Core with the Enterprise Addons:

mkdir -p ~/odoo-deployment && cd ~/odoo-deployment

# 1. Download Odoo 19.0 Stable Core
git clone https://github.com/odoo/odoo.git --depth 1 --branch 19.0 core_temp
mv core_temp/* . && rm -rf core_temp

# 2. Add Enterprise Addons (Clone your enterprise repo here)
# Replace the URL with your actual enterprise modules source
git clone https://github.com/your-user/your-enterprise-repo.git enterprise_addons

⚙️ 3. Configuration Files

A. Dockerfile

This file patches Odoo 19 to be compatible with Python 3.12 and Werkzeug 2.x
libraries.

FROM python:3.12-slim-bookworm
ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
ENV LC_ALL=C.UTF-8

# System dependencies
RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
    ca-certificates curl fonts-noto-cjk node-less npm libssl-dev \
    xz-utils libxml2-dev libxslt1-dev libldap2-dev libsasl2-dev \
    libpq-dev libjpeg-dev libwebp-dev build-essential git \
    && curl -o wkhtmltox.deb -sSL https://github.com/wkhtmltopdf/packaging/releases/download/0.12.6.1-3/wkhtmltox_0.12.6.1-3.bookworm_amd64.deb \
    && apt-get install -y ./wkhtmltox.deb \
    && rm wkhtmltox.deb && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

RUN npm install -g rtlcss
RUN useradd -m -U -r -d /opt/odoo -s /bin/bash odoo
WORKDIR /opt/odoo

# Install Python requirements with specific patches for Odoo 19
COPY requirements.txt .
RUN pip install --no-cache-dir --upgrade pip && \
    pip install --no-cache-dir "Werkzeug<3.0.0" && \
    pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt && \
    pip install --no-cache-dir gevent

COPY . .

USER root
RUN chmod +x odoo-bin && chown -R odoo:odoo /opt/odoo
USER odoo
EXPOSE 8069
ENTRYPOINT ["/opt/odoo/odoo-bin"]
CMD ["-c", "/etc/odoo/odoo.conf"]

B. odoo.conf

Adjust addons_path to include your enterprise directory.

[options]
addons_path = /opt/odoo/enterprise_addons,/opt/odoo/addons,/opt/odoo/odoo/addons
data_dir = /var/lib/odoo
admin_passwd = REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_MASTER_PASSWORD
db_host = db
db_user = odoo
db_password = odoo
db_port = 5432
http_interface = 0.0.0.0
proxy_mode = True

C. docker-compose.yml

Uses Caddy for automatic SSL.

services:
  web:
    build: .
    container_name: odoo_app
    restart: always
    depends_on:
      - db
    volumes:
      - odoo-data:/var/lib/odoo
      - ./odoo.conf:/etc/odoo/odoo.conf
    environment:
      - HOST=db
      - USER=odoo
      - PASSWORD=odoo

  db:
    image: postgres:16-alpine
    container_name: odoo_db
    restart: always
    environment:
      - POSTGRES_DB=postgres
      - POSTGRES_PASSWORD=odoo
      - POSTGRES_USER=odoo
    volumes:
      - db-data:/var/lib/postgresql/data

  proxy:
    image: caddy:latest
    container_name: caddy_proxy
    restart: always
    ports:
      - "80:80"
      - "443:443"
    command: caddy reverse-proxy --from odoo.example.com --to web:8069
    depends_on:
      - web

volumes:
  odoo-data:
  db-data:

🚀 4. Deployment

1.  Build the image:

    sudo docker compose build --no-cache

2.  Start the services:

    sudo docker compose up -d

3.  Fix Permissions (Optional but recommended): If you see a Permission Denied
    error in logs, run:

    sudo docker exec -u root odoo_app chown -R odoo:odoo /var/lib/odoo

✅ 5. Final Steps

1.  Open https://odoo.example.com in your browser.
2.  Create your database using the Master Password set in odoo.conf.
3.  Go to Apps, click "Update Apps List", and install "Accounting" or "Web
    Enterprise" to activate Enterprise features.

🛠️ Troubleshooting

  - SSL not working: Ensure ports 80 and 443 are open in your VPS firewall.
  - Internal Server Error 500: Check logs with sudo docker compose logs -f web.
    Usually related to missing Python libraries or Werkzeug version mismatch.
  - Persistence: All Odoo data is stored in Docker volumes. Back them up
    regularly!

